Finger Control (PC Side) — README
This repo provides a PC-side Python controller for one or more Arduino-based “fingers” over USB serial.

It supports:
Background reading + logging (one process per finger)

Warmup/config handshake (WARMUP → CFG)
Run gating (must START before sending targets)
20 Hz status stream (STAT,... from Arduino)


Teach modes
TEACH_ALL (motor + servos passive)
TEACH_SERVOS (servos passive, motor holds position)

Pose capture & replay:

POSE (read current pose)
SAVE <name> (save current pose into poses.yaml)
RUN <name> (send the saved pose as a command)


#!/usr/bin/env python3
# Python 3.8 compatible
# pip install pyserial loguru pyyaml
#
# Usage:
# REMEMBER
#   conda activate vtIL
#   ls /dev/tty*
#   ./chmod_usb.sh
#   python finger_control.py fingers.yaml
#
# YAML example:
# outputs_root: outputs
# baud: 115200
# cfg_timeout_s: 6.0
# boot_delay_s: 2.0
# fingers:
#   - index: 1
#     port: /dev/ttyUSB0
#     name: finger_1